concept.title: CYLINDER Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates a 3D solid in the shape of a cylinder.

p.note: In BricsCAD Classic, which doesn’t support 3D solids, the CYLINDER command launches the .

conbody.p: Create a 3D solid in the shape of a circular or elliptical cylinder. Choose from a combination of options including center, radius, diameter, 3 point, 2 point, tangents, axis endpoints, and height.

section.title: Methods to create a cylinder
section.p: There are 5 methods to begin creating a cylinder:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a circular cylinder by specifying the center of the base then:
Specify the radius of the cylinder.
Additional option: [Diameter]
Specify the height of the cylinder.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint]
Begin creating a circular cylinder by specifying the first of three points on the circumference of its base then:
Specify the second point on the circumference.
Specify the third point on the circumference.
Specify the height of the cylinder.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint]
Begin creating a circular cylinder by specifying the first of two points on the circumference of its base then:
Specify the second point on the diameter. The two points define the diameter of the base.
Specify the height of the cylinder.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint]
Begin creating a cylinder by selecting a tangent point on the first entity then:

dlentry.dt: Specify point on object for second tangent
dlentry.dd: Select a tangent point on the second entity.
Specify a valid radius for the base. If you specify a radius that is not possible with the selected tangents, you are prompted to specify the tangents and radius again.
Specify the height of the cylinder.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint]
Begin creating an elliptical cylinder by specifying the first end of the ellipse axis then:
Alternate option: [Center]
Specify the second end of the ellipse axis.
Specify the radius of the other ellipse axis.
Specify the height of the cylinder.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint]

section.title: Options within the CYLINDER command
section.p: After you begin creating a cylinder, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the height of the cylinder as the distance between any two points.
Specify axis endpoint to define the height and orientation of the cylinder in 3D space. The center of the base is used as the other axis endpoint.
Specify the diameter of the cylinder’s base.
